<p>I'm trying to write CSS stylesheet dynamically but Flex 4 requires that you declare the namespace in the Style markup.  </p>  <p>If I have a Spark Button or MX Button class or class instance how would I get the namespace of that button? </p>  <p>So far I've tried this:  </p>  <pre><code>var className:Object = getQualifiedClassName(myButton); var ButtonClass:Object = ApplicationDomain.currentDomain.getDefinition(className); var button:Object = new ButtonClass(); </code></pre>  <p>With that information I can write this:  </p>  <pre><code>&lt;fx:Style&gt;      myButton {         color: red;     }  &lt;/fx:Style&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I need to create this:  </p>  <pre><code>&lt;fx:Style&gt;     @namespace s "library://ns.adobe.com/flex/spark";     @namespace mx "library://ns.adobe.com/flex/mx";      s|Button {         color: red;     }  &lt;/fx:Style&gt; </code></pre>